Be extremely careful with the 'frame' tool: only use it on a single, unframed item, or it will be ruined. The 'scissors' tool is risky; it sometimes lessens negative values on 'overcomplicated' items, but often decreases the value of positive items or makes negative items even worse. message: Hello future crafter! I found a consistent way to reach a score of 45. First, use the 'frame' tool on a single natural, soft item like a 'leaf' or 'sunflower' to get 20 points. Second, combine a 'hard' ingredient (natural or artificial) with a 'soft artificial' ingredient (e.g., 'wood' + 'thread', or 'acorn' + 'ribbon') to make a hybrid (usually 30 points).
